Interface Sender

    • Method Detail

      • sendMessage

        void sendMessage(String string)
        Send a message to the sender.
        Parameters:
        string - text to send.

      • sendMessage

        void sendMessage(String[] strings)
        Send multiple messages to the sender.
        Parameters:
        strings - Array of text to send, each element is sent as a separate message.

      • sendLink

        void sendLink(String pretext,
              String linkText,
              String url)
        Send a link to the sender.
        Parameters:
        pretext - Text to display before the actual link. Not displayed on console.
        linkText - Text to display as the link, underlined. Not displayed on console.
        url - URL to point to.

      • sendLink

        default void sendLink(String linkText,
                      String url)
        Send a link to the sender without a pretext.
        Parameters:
        linkText - Text to display as the link, underlined. Not displayed on console.
        url - URL to point to.

      • getName

        String getName()
        Get the name of the sender, defined by delegated sender object.
        Returns:
        Name returned by sender defined by the server platform.

      • hasPermission

        boolean hasPermission(String string)
        Does the sender have a permission, defined by delegated sender object.
        Parameters:
        string - Permission node.
        Returns:
        true/false returned by sender defined by the server platform.

      • isOp

        boolean isOp()
        Check if the sender has OP status.
        Returns:
        true/false returned by sender defined by the server platform. Some platforms do not have concept of OP.

      • getSenderType

        SenderType getSenderType()
        Get what kind of a sender this object is.
        Returns:
        One of SenderType enum values.

      • getSender

        Object getSender()
        Get the delegated sender object.
        Returns:
        sender defined by the server platform.
